Ask HN: Google Ads account suspended immediately after creation, what can I do?
text:
I recently created a Google Ads account to promote my SaaS. After signing up, you immediately start out creating a new campaign, which was a bit overwhelming. I left the browser tab open and returned to it after a while, filling in the required fields to the best of my knowledge, knowing that surely I would be able to correct them later.

Funnily, or not so funny for me, the account was suspended just a day afterwards for "Circumventing Systems". I haven't even started a campaign yet, not sure what I could be "circumventing". I filed an appeal a week ago but haven't received an answer yet. In the console, the "file an appeal" button is still active, but I'm hesitant to file a second one, at the risk of being too pushy.

Any advice on how to proceed? I'm using my main Google Workspace business account.

title: Ask HN: What projects can new programmers build to gain more confidence?
text:
We often hear that building small to moderate size projects make you more confident as a programmer than reading books or taking courses.

Suppose a newly minted programmer who has taken an introductory course on Programming and/or Computer Science somewhere and knows the basic constructs of a programming language.

What projects can such a person build? Is there a list that is suitable for a beginner like that?

Ask HN: Coming from a non-CS field into machine learning research?
text:
There are many grad students who have done their bachelor's degree in a field that is not computer science. But in grad school they are doing fantastic research work in the field of machine learning or deep learning. Not only in grad school but in R&D labs, too.

If you are someone like that what made you choose that path? I presume you had to self teach a lot of things during the switch e.g: programming, more math?

Can you describe your story for us?
